  "title": "Tax Associate",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company: Cypress Singapore PAC</strong></p><p>Cypress Policy of Trust & Empowerment allows flexible working arrangements that allow lifestyle choices and managing childcare or eldercare needs. Workloads will be allocated taking into consideration each candidate’s situation<strong>. </strong>Cypress adopts a one-on-one mentoring program with junior staff to guide and enrich them with work-related training.</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Job Title: Tax Associate</strong></p><p><br /></p><p><u>Duties and Responsibilities:</u></p><p>· Deliver high-quality and professional tax computations for both Singapore, catering to a portfolio of international clients and SMEs across various industries.</p><p>· Preparation of Singapore corporate tax computations & returns in compliance with Singapore and Malaysian tax regulations.</p><p>· Ensure adherence to tax filing deadlines.</p><p>· Support in tax-related queries, and appeals </p><p>· Assist clients in responding to enquiries from the Singapore tax authorities.</p><p><u>Position Requirements:</u></p><p>· A bachelor’s degree in accounting, Taxation, Finance, or a related discipline is required.</p><p>· Proficiency in the tax regulations of Singapore is a prerequisite.</p><p>· Strong competency in Microsoft Excel is essential, and familiarity with tax software such as Singtax is advantageous.</p><p>· Fluency in English, both in verbal and written communication, is required.</p><p>· A commitment to remaining informed about changing tax regulations is necessary.</p><p>· Candidates must demonstrate effective communication and interpersonal skills and the ability to collaborate with colleagues at all levels.</p><p>· The ability to work autonomously and consistently to implement proactive initiatives is essential.</p>",
